# Git: branch + PR, Conventional Commits

`main` is live. Argo CD auto-syncs this repo’s App-of-apps chart from the default branch; commits on `main` can change the cluster immediately.

- Do not commit or push to `main`.
- Use a feature branch, push it, and open a PR (`gh pr create`).
- Commit messages and PR titles use Conventional Commits: `type(optional-scope): description` (e.g. `feat(vault): …`, `docs(agents): …`).
- Merges to `main` are squash-only — keep the PR title conventional.
- Full workflow: `docs/agents/git-workflow.md`.
